<p>
<i>Scientific Notation</i> is a method of representing very large or
 very small numbers in a compact way
without losing precision.
</p>
<p>
Scientific notation always uses both a <a href="glossary.php?term=coefficient">coefficient</a>, which
can be an integer or a floating point number, and an 
<a href="glossary.php?term=exponent">exponent</a>, which can be positive or negative.</p>